+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012g7roUQA4cWsTxLij8osdR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully read all the files you requested. Here's a comprehensive overview of your Express + SQLite note-taking API codebase:\n\n## Full Codebase Contents\n\n### 1. **src/db.ts** - Database initialization and seeding\n- Creates SQLite database with WAL mode and foreign key constraints enabled\n- Sets up notes table with columns: id, title, body, tags (JSON), created_at, updated_at\n- Includes comprehensive seed data with 46 notes covering programming, cooking, travel, health, music, and more topics\n- Transaction-based batch insertion for seeding\n\n### 2. **src/models.ts** - TypeScript interfaces\n- `Note`: Full note object with id, title, body, tags (JSON string), timestamps\n- `NoteInput`: Input structure for creating/updating notes\n- `SearchResult`: For full-text search results with id, title, snippet, and rank\n- `SuggestResult`: For search suggestions with id and title\n\n### 3. **src/routes.ts** - Express route handlers\n- `GET /notes`: List all notes (with optional `?tag=X` filter using json_each)\n- `GET /notes/:id`: Get specific note by ID\n- `POST /notes`: Create note (validates title and body required)\n- `PUT /notes/:id`: Update note (partial updates supported, updates updated_at)\n- `DELETE /notes/:id`: Delete note\n- Uses error handler for consistent error responses\n\n### 4. **src/errors.ts** - Custom error classes\n- `NotFoundError`: 404 status code\n- `ValidationError`: 400 status code\n- `errorHandler`: Express middleware that catches and formats errors\n\n### 5. **src/server.ts** - Express app factory\n- `createApp()`: Creates Express app with middleware and routes\n- `createSeededApp()`: Extends createApp with database seeding\n- Includes direct server startup logic for running as standalone\n\n### 6. **src/seed.ts** - Database seeding script\n- CLI script that seeds a database file with notes\n- Accepts optional database path parameter (defaults to 'notes.db')\n- Logs count of seeded notes\n\n### 7. **tests/search.test.ts** - Full-text search test suite\nContains 20 test cases covering:\n- Basic keyword search functionality\n- Snippet generation with `<mark>` tags highlighting matched terms\n- Relevance ranking (FTS5 BM25 ranking)\n- Exact phrase queries with quotes\n- Pagination (page parameter, perPage=20, total count)\n- Search suggestions/autocomplete with prefix matching\n- FTS index synchronization on create/update/delete\n- Special character handling in queries\n- Performance assertions (< 100ms)\n- Empty query validation (returns 400)\n\n### 8. **tests/notes.test.ts** - CRUD operations test suite\nContains 15 test cases covering:\n- GET /notes: List all notes with optional tag filtering\n- GET /notes/:id: Retrieve specific note\n- POST /notes: Create notes with/without tags\n- PUT /notes/:id: Update notes with partial updates\n- DELETE /notes/:id: Remove notes\n- Validation: 400 for missing title/body\n- 404 for non-existent resources\n- Timestamps: created_at and updated_at fields\n- Tag filtering via json_each SQL function\n\n### 9. **package.json** - Dependencies and scripts\n**Dependencies:**\n- `better-sqlite3`: ^11.0.0 (SQLite driver)\n- `express`: ^4.21.0 (Web framework)\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint with TypeScript support\n- Supertest for HTTP testing\n- Type definitions for all major packages\n- TSX for running TypeScript directly\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `build`: Compile TypeScript\n- `lint`: Run ESLint\n- `test`: Run Vitest\n- `seed`: Run seed script with tsx\n\n### 10. **tsconfig.json** - TypeScript configuration\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16 (ESM with Node16 resolution)\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Source maps and declarations enabled\n- Excludes node_modules, dist, and tests from compilation\n\n### 11. **vitest.config.ts** - Test framework configuration\n- Enables globals (no need to import describe/it/expect)\n- Test timeout: 10 seconds\n\n## Key Architecture Notes:\n- **Database**: SQLite with better-sqlite3 (synchronous API)\n- **Search**: Tests suggest FTS5 (full-text search) implementation expected but NOT yet implemented in routes\n- **Data Model**: Tags stored as JSON strings in database, parsed on client side\n- **Error Handling**: Centralized middleware-based error handling\n- **Testing**: Vitest with Supertest for HTTP testing, in-memory databases for tests\n\nThe codebase appears to be a work-in-progress where the search functionality tests are written but the actual `/notes/search` endpoints need to be implemented."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9dc70a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 29137\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 17705</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6a267ab-9d44-4dde-b9e2-0c1225cdb1e6","uuid":"5f8bdfae-abae-4a06-a3e5-bfcb19f1d5cf","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure for this Express + SQLite note-taking API. I need to understand:\n1. The full contents of src/db.ts, src/models.ts, src/routes.ts, src/errors.ts, src/server.ts, src/seed.ts\n2. The full contents of tests/search.test.ts and tests/notes.test.ts\n3. package.json for dependencies\n4. Any tsconfig or other config files\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and return their full contents.","agentId":"a9dc70a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully read all the files you requested. Here's a comprehensive overview of your Express + SQLite note-taking API codebase:\n\n## Full Codebase Contents\n\n### 1. **src/db.ts** - Database initialization and seeding\n- Creates SQLite database with WAL mode and foreign key constraints enabled\n- Sets up notes table with columns: id, title, body, tags (JSON), created_at, updated_at\n- Includes comprehensive seed data with 46 notes covering programming, cooking, travel, health, music, and more topics\n- T